eless.</p><p>The marketing landscape is to diverse &amp; so large that it seems evoking direct user feedback is the most efficient means of cleaning up the linkspam.  Can&#8217;t say I blame you for trying, but it will be interesting to see who/what is being reported through the system.</p><p>Hopefully the feedback you do receive will prove beneficial to the end users &amp; the search results overall.</p><p>Thanks for sharing.</p></div></dd><dt class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-485889"> <span class="avatar"><a href="http://centuryhouse.net/" rel="external nofollow"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/5e1788073d730dbdd0c4f8ac4601e88a?s=44&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /></a></span> <span class="comment_author"><a href='http://centuryhouse.net/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Robert Enriquez</a></span> <span class="comment_time"><a href="#comment-485889" title="Permalink to this comment" rel="nofollow">March 3, 2010 at 12:33 pm</a></span></dt><dd class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1"><div class="format_text" id="comment-body-485889"><p>Matt &#8211; one more thing</p><p>If someone reports any of your site(s), and YOU receive the report&#8230;do you recuse yourself and hand it to someone else? <img src='http://www.mattcutts.com/blog/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_razz.gif' alt=':P' class='wp-smiley' /></p></div></dd><dt class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-485890"> <span class="avatar"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/53a248545cd591a5c94d06afb2314492?s=44&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /></span> <span class="comment_author">alex</span> <span class="comment_time"><a href="#comment-485890" title="Permalink to this comment" rel="nofollow">March 3, 2010 at 12:33 pm</a></span></dt><dd class="comment even thread-even depth-1"><div class="format_text" id="comment-body-485890"><p>you have to