 make Google more money? Maybe in some indirect way, but the main benefit in my mind is that I see less spam in the future (and presumably other email users will see less spam too).</p></div></dd><dt class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-485950"> <span class="avatar"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/809301a27e620e15e1320f42de3532df?s=44&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /></span> <span class="comment_author">Robert</span> <span class="comment_time"><a href="#comment-485950" title="Permalink to this comment" rel="nofollow">March 3, 2010 at 1:19 pm</a></span></dt><dd class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1"><div class="format_text" id="comment-body-485950"><p>I totally agree with Lester&#8230; There are these mom &amp; pop shops that will be hurt, but if there is some way for them to know that this penalty has been put against them, then they can react to that to solve the problem. Perhaps putting that into place is the only fair way to do this &#8211; or at least a step in the direction of fair.</p></div></dd><dt class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-485953"> <span class="avatar"><a href="http://potpolitics.com/2010/03/03/googles-hidden-isosceles-project/" rel="external nofollow"><img alt='' src='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/7c2f16dbf0444a5e07d5dbd8715bdaaf?s=44&amp;d=identicon&amp;r=G' class='avatar avatar-44 photo' height='44' width='44' /></a></span> <span class="comment_author"><a href='http://potpolitics.com/2010/03/03/googles-hidden-isosceles-project/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>John Sullivan</a></span> <span class="comment_time"><a href="#comment-485953" title="Permalink to this comment" rel="nofollow">March 3, 2010 at 1:23 pm</a></span></dt><dd class="comment even thread-even depth-1"><div class="format_text" id="comment-body-485953"><p>Matt I was disappointed you didn&#8217;t approve my comment and left it in moderation and went on appro